{"id":16085,"title":"[Health problems of combatants during the First World War].","abstract":"The First World War because of the use of new weapons, injured more than 3 500 000 people (500 000 in the face), more than diseases (tuberculosis, typhoid fever, etc.) or even weather circumstances. The healing of the war wounds through surgery undertook a significant evolution thanks to the use of asepsis and antiseptics. Mortality go down, opening the way to the physical and psychological rehabilitation of those injured by the war.","date":"2014-07-29","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25069353","annotations":[{"name":"Typhoid fever","weight":0.874845,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Typhoid_fever"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.750806,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Tuberculosis","weight":0.721372,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuberculosis"},{"name":"Mortality rate","weight":0.704585,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mortality_rate"},{"name":"Fever","weight":0.675714,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fever"},{"name":"Evolution","weight":0.670603,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolution"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.609634,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Health","weight":0.583977,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Antiseptic","weight":0.546519,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antiseptic"},{"name":"Asepsis","weight":0.435248,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asepsis"},{"name":"World War I","weight":0.408889,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_I"},{"name":"Psychology","weight":0.408055,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology"},{"name":"Physical therapy","weight":0.348337,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_therap